<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1036,1315]" pageId="10" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,933,1036,1063]" pageId="10" pageNumber="356">
Additional information in description (Female 
<typeStatus box="[721,832,1037,1063]" pageId="10" pageNumber="356">Holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<figureCitation box="[846,918,1036,1063]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1913,1938]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,1350,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1437,1350,1869]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lophotettix zumbadoi Barranco, 2010 right lateral view of holotype. Photo of type: Pablo Barranco." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491600/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="356">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
):
</emphasis>
Facial carina and conspicuous frontal costa bifurcation visible; infrascapular area narrow, femur robust and with small lappets throughout dorsal and external margins.
</paragraph>
